# MARS – environment variables for LLM providers
# Copy this file to .env and fill in the keys you have.
# The CLI auto-loads .env on startup (no extra packages needed).
#
# ── EASIEST: GITHUB MODELS (free, uses your existing GitHub account) ─────────
#
# 1. Go to  https://github.com/settings/tokens
# 2. Click  "Generate new token (classic)"
# 3. Give it any name (e.g. "MARS"), no extra scopes needed
# 4. Click  "Generate token" and copy the value (starts with ghp_)
# 5. Paste it below:
#
# GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
#
# Then start the CLI with:
#   python -m mars.cli.main --provider github-models
#   python -m mars.cli.main --provider github-models --model meta-llama-3.3-70b-instruct
#   python -m mars.cli.main --provider github-models --model phi-4
#
# Available models: gpt-4o, gpt-4o-mini, o1-mini, o3-mini,
#   meta-llama-3.3-70b-instruct, meta-llama-3.1-8b-instruct,
#   phi-4, phi-4-mini-instruct, mistral-large-2411, mistral-nemo
#
# ── OTHER FREE CLOUD PROVIDERS ──────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# OpenRouter  https://openrouter.ai/keys  (many :free models)
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
#
# Groq  https://console.groq.com  (llama3, gemma – very fast)
# GROQ_API_KEY=gsk_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
#
# Gemini  https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
# GOOGLE_API_KEY=AIzaxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
#
# Cerebras  https://cloud.cerebras.ai  (llama3 – extremely fast)
# CEREBRAS_API_KEY=csk-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
#
# ── LOCAL (completely free, runs on your machine) ───────────────────────────
#
# Ollama  https://ollama.com  →  ollama serve  +  ollama pull llama3.2
# LM Studio  https://lmstudio.ai  →  start local server in the app
# (no key needed for either)
#
# ── PAID ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# Copy this file to .env and fill in the keys you have.
# The CLI auto-loads .env on startup (no extra packages needed).
#
# ── FREE / NO CREDIT CARD REQUIRED ─────────────────────────────────────────
#
# GitHub Copilot  (if you have a Copilot subscription)
#   Get token: Settings → Developer settings → Personal access tokens
#   Required scope: (none extra – your normal GitHub token works)
# GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
#
# OpenRouter  https://openrouter.ai/keys  (many free models available)
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
#
# Groq  https://console.groq.com  (llama3, gemma, mixtral – fast & free)
# GROQ_API_KEY=gsk_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
#
# Gemini  https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey  (Gemini 2.0 Flash free)
# GOOGLE_API_KEY=AIzaxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
#
# Cerebras  https://cloud.cerebras.ai  (llama3 – very fast free tier)
# CEREBRAS_API_KEY=csk-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
#
# ── LOCAL (completely free, runs on your machine) ───────────────────────────
#
# Ollama  https://ollama.com  (pull any open model: ollama pull llama3.2)
# No key needed – just start: ollama serve
#
# LM Studio  https://lmstudio.ai  (GUI for local models)
# No key needed – just start the local server in LM Studio
#
# ── PAID ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# OpenAI  https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
#
# Anthropic  https://console.anthropic.com
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
#
# ── USAGE ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Start CLI with a specific provider:
#   python -m mars.cli.main --provider copilot
#   python -m mars.cli.main --provider openrouter --model meta-llama/llama-3.3-70b-instruct:free
#   python -m mars.cli.main --provider groq --model llama-3.3-70b-versatile
#   python -m mars.cli.main --provider ollama --model llama3.2
#   python -m mars.cli.main --provider mock          # no key, for testing
#
# Or use /spawn inside the CLI:
#   /spawn copilot
#   /spawn openrouter meta-llama/llama-3.3-70b-instruct:free
#   /spawn groq llama-3.3-70b-versatile
#   /spawn mock
